data.name: ConfigDescriptionAnnotationTransformFilePath
data.value: Specifies an XSLT transformation file that is used to translate inline schema documentation into the schemaDoc element.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionDocFilePaths
data.value: Specifies additional documentation files to be used.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionDocumentConstraints
data.value: If true, the element constraints xs:unique, xs:key, and xs:keyref are documented.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionDocumentRootElements
data.value: If true, the root elements get their own entry in the table of contents.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionDocumentRootSchemas
data.value: If true, the root schemas get their own entry in the table of contents. Please note that DocumentSchemas must be set to true for this setting to be effective.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionDocumentSchemas
data.value: If true, the schemas get their own entry in the table of contents.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionDocumentSyntax
data.value: If true, every element, attribute, group, attribute group, complex type, and simple type topic contains a section showing their XSD declaration.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionIncludeLinkUriInKeywordK
data.value: Specifies whether XML entity links such as "http://schemas.example.org#E/myElement/@myAttribute" are included in the K keyword index. This allows programmatically navigating the help file to a topic describing a given XML entity.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionNamespaceContainer
data.value: If true, a namespace table of content entry will be created as the container of the namespace contents in the documented schema set. If false, the namespace contents are listed directly. Please note that this setting is ignored if the schema set contains more than one namespace. In that case, every namespace will always have a table of content entry.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionSchemaDependencyFilePaths
data.value: Specifies the schema files the schema set will depend on. They will be added to the internal schema set in order to be able to process it but these schemas will not being documented.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionSchemaFilePaths
data.value: Specifies the schema files that are part of the schema set.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionSchemaSetContainer
data.value: If true, a root "Schema Set" table of content entry will be created as the container of the namespaces in the documented schema set. If false, the default, the namespaces are listed in the table of content as root entries.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionSchemaSetTitle
data.value: An alternate title for the "Schema Set" page and the root table of content container.

data.name: ConfigDescriptionSortOrder
data.value: This defines the sort order for merging the XML schema topics with the main help file.
